    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** as our definitive anchor, boasting a commanding 83.29 efficiency score. His matchup against Houser is ideal; the combination of a +16% park factor and the optimal leadoff spot makes him a high-ceiling play for both R and SB potential. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.87) also presents a strong profile, **Gunnar Henderson**\u2019s aggressive positioning in the order against a mid-tier arm provides the highest cumulative value for our 5x5 Roto chase. **Heliot Ramos** (61.05) and **Miguel Vargas** (60.61) also warrant attention; both benefit significantly from park factors and order placement, serving as high-floor starters despite the moderate SP_xERA figures they face.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Josh Jung**, who arrived at a 57.03 score. Despite a highly favorable matchup against the struggling Sasaki (5.52 xERA) and a massive 19% SP skill advantage, **Josh Jung** was ultimately edged out by the superior plate appearance quality projected for **Jorge Polanco** and **Drake Baldwin**. The optimizer prioritized the lineup stability of the latter two over the upside of **Josh Jung**, whose efficiency was hampered by a lower-tier batting order position. Meanwhile, caution is advised regarding **Kyle Tucker** (57.75) and **Andy Pages** (48.40); both face the formidable deGrom. While **Kyle Tucker** remains a mandatory start due to his elite baseline, his score is suppressed by deGrom\u2019s suppressed SP skill, making them our highest-risk assets today.",
